nodes.bodyText:
I think it's a bit awkward to return the list of instances whose deletion failed; usually these methods don't return anything, or they return the list of instances whose deletion succeeded.
how about we keep it as void, and only log one line at the end if there are any instances whose deletion failed? that way we persist the information we need while being concise.
just to cut down on back-and-forth, this is what I mean:
for-each {
    try {
        dropInstance();
    } catch (Exception e) {
        failedDeletions.add(instanceName);
    }
}
if (failedDeletions.size > 0) {
    LOG.error("ZKHelixAdmin::purgeOfflineInstances(): failed to drop the following instances: " + failedDeletions);
}

quick, concise, has all the information we need, and don't pollute the log if there are a lot of failures. what do you think?

